body:
Chapter Two | Two Weeks

- the series where Y/N and Harry aren’t much fond of each other 

A/N: Please head to my master list for Chapter One. Tumblr isn’t tagging my post if I use any links!

“I don’t think I have to tell you this, but -”

Y/N was trying to stuff few of her books in her bag when Jake spoke.

“Hm?” Y/N didn’t look up at him, she was too busy with her books and her bag.

“Stay away from Harry.”

Y/N came to an halt hearing that.

“Huh?” she was confused really, why was her uncle saying that, all of a sudden. She clearly remembered the ‘she’s off limit’ thing he said to Harry, but Jake also knew she didn’t really like him

“What are you talking about,” she returned to zip her bag full of books. She was pretty sure her shoulder would be sore for carrying it but she had to return those books to the college library by that day.

“Harry, he- just stay away from him,” Jake said again.

“Why? I mean isn’t he ‘such a nice guy’,” Y/N said nonchalantly, not bothering to look up at him.

“He is but, you know - there’s media involved, and his fans can be pretty aggressive and I don’t think it’ll work out. I mean he’s good guy but I don’t want you to get hurt ag-” Jake rambled on but Y/N quickly cut him off.

“Okay, calm down,” she hung the bag on her back and let out a groan. It was heavier than she thought it’d be.“I’m really not interested.”

“Where is the ‘nice guy’, anyway?” She made her way towards the door

“He had work in his studio.”

Y/N nodded, but she truly didn’t care.

“See you later,” she called.

She heard Jake and Clare both call back from inside the house before she shut the door.

*

“Enough already!” Y/N’s best friend, Emilia exclaimed but her voice was just audible for Y/N to hear.

“What?” Y/N asked clearly clueless as she flipped few pages of the new book she just took from the library shelf.

“All you do is read, can you not take a break?” Emilia huffed, poking on the new thousand pages book - just about the evolution of architectures over time.

“It’s fun,” she replied.

“It’s not fun,” Emilia paused. “But, I can show you what real fun is…”

However, Emilia didn’t have to speak further for making Y/N understand what she was suggesting.

“Nope, I’m not going,” she said dismissively.

“Oh c'mon!” Emilia pleaded. “It won’t be for too long! We’ll drop you off by midnight!”

“No, Emilia. I’m nothing going,” Y/N scrolled through her book trying to take in all the subjects and architecture monuments it talked about. “And you said in a way, it almost sounded as if your suggesting something…”

Emilia didn’t reply to that or said anything at all for a while. Y/N almost thought she gave up but was she wrong.

“Tom!” she yelled making everyone in the library look at her with wide eyes, including Y/N and except Tom. He had a pair of headphones on.

“What are you doing?” Y/N whispered yelled as she looked at Mrs. Valenta the librarian across the room strolling towards them. Emilia didn’t bother to reply. She just got up and pulled Y/N up with her. This made Mrs. Valenta stop on her way and, look at them skeptically.

“Wait!” Y/N exclaimed pulling her hand away from Emilia’s and grabbing her bag, closing the book on the process. Y/N thought they were leaving but surely Emilia had different plans.

“I know you have a little crush on him!” she whispered with a smirk.

“What?” Y/N said dumb founded, her heart beat rising slightly - how could she have known?

“Don’t act stupid, I saw how you look at him,” Emilia let out a chuckle.

Y/N rolled her eyes, “yeah right!” Even though Y/N was pretty sure that she didn’t look at him any differently, she was still a little scared. She didn’t want him or anyone to know about this.

Y/N looked up at Mrs. Valenta who had gone back to her sit, thinking they were leaving. Y/N thought that too but that was until Emilia dragged Y/N to where Tom was sitting the she was about to walk out of the room. However, if Y/N was honest she was kindof expecting this.

“Hola,” Emilia patted Tom’s back as she sat next to him, almost startling him. Y/N walked around the table and took the sit across them.

“Hey,” he said to both of them, of course a little confused.

“So, I heard you’re going to the party Lilly’s having tonight?” Emilia asked him making Y/N roll her eyes.

“Uh, yeah….?” Tom said uncertainly.

“Well, I was trying to get Y/N come with me, but she wouldn’t come,” she paused. “So, I was hoping you’d help me out here. I mean both of you love books, but Y/N look - even he likes to go to party every now and then!”

“Actually, I don’t want to go either, Lucas -he’s sorta forcing me.”

This made Emilia’s face palm and Y/N giggle. However, Tom quickly added looking at Y/N with a smile, “but you can come you know, I’ll find someone to hangout with.”

“I don’t think I’ll come,” Y/N said. Still smiling slightly she got up from her chair.

“C'mon, Y/N one party,” Emilia insisted but Y/N pressed her lips together and shook her head. Nevertheless it was enough for Emilia to shut up.

*

“I’m home,” Y/N said happily as she entered the house and closed the door behind her.

It was almost 9 pm when she returned. Both her uncle and aunt were cuddled up on the couch, binge watching some tv shows. Ice Cream was peacefully snoozing on the floor- however she woke up just the second she heard Y/N’s voice.

Y/N’s college had ended a long time ago but she decided to go to a coffee shop to finish an assignment that she had. Or maybe she just didn’t want to see Harry’s face or be in his presence at all -everything about him annoyed her, even thinking about him for a split second made her scrunch her nose in annoyance. Y/N knew she shouldn’t be this judgmental as she met him just the night before and for couple of minutes only. But she couldn’t help herself, something about him just made her not like him.

As Y/N expected she hadn’t ran into Harry in the coffee shop, nonetheless she had ran into Tom.

Y/N was typing away furiously on her laptop when he had approached her. Y/N had her eyebrows knitted together; her notebook was carelessly lying near her with all the bullet points about the assignment.

“May I sit here,” Tom had said, but Y/N was too busy to recognize his voice. She was about shoo away whoever it was, but that was until she realized who it was.

Y/N had looked at his face for a while. A bit shocked - not expecting to see him there and then contemplating whether to say yes or not.

“Uh yeah,” she had stuttered out after a while gesturing to the sit across her. Tom had happily sat down and started a conversation about college and what she was doing. At first it was just about college but then they started talking about personal stuffs -what they liked, what they didn’t, their families.

By 8, they had another mug of hot chocolate and Tom ended up sitting next to her in excuse of seeing what she was doing.

Y/N had finished half of the assignment after sitting there for five hours. Y/N knew she would’ve finished the whole thing, if Tom hadn’t interrupted but she wasn’t complaining - she had a little crush on him after all.

“Welcome home, Y/N,” Clare said from the couch.

“Someone’s glowing, what happened?” Jake asked seeing the bright smile on her face.

“Nothing,” she shook her head, but she couldn’t shake of the huge smile.

“C'mere, Iccy!” Y/N gestured Ice Cream to follow her upstairs, who was on her feet almost instantly, moving her tail happily.

Y/N slowly made her way up the stairs, Ice Cream hot on her trail.

“You missed me, buddy?” Y/N said looking down at the 3 years old Samoyed as she earned a loud bark from her.

Y/N laughed. She knew how clingy she was and she knew the only thing Ice Cream wanted to do then was cuddle her. And she didn’t mind that. Y/N was about to take the turn towards her room but that is when she smashed into something hard making her stumble a little backward; the back of her leg coming in contact with Ice Creams body made her lose control. She was about fall on her butt and probably over Ice Cream but Y/N quickly grabbed the stairs railing as Ice Cream moved away from her spot.

“I’m so sorry! Are you okay?” Harry asked. He had both of his hands extended towards her - probably to grab her incase she hadn’t gotten hold of the railings. He wore a horrified look on his face.

“Was okay,” Y/N mumbled walking past Harry and into her room.

“Hey, I’m really sorry about that wasn’t looking where I was going,” Harry said. But the moment Ice Cream had entered her room, she quickly shut the door without looking up at him.

And there, she shut the door on his face for the second time, leaving him clueless in the hallway.

She really didn’t like him.

This made Emilia’s face palm and Y/N giggle. However, Tom quickly added looking at Y/N with a smile, “but you can come you know, I’ll find someone to hangout with.”

“I don’t think I’ll come,” Y/N said. Still smiling slightly she got up from her chair.

“C'mon, Y/N one party,” Emilia insisted but Y/N pressed her lips together and shook her head. Nevertheless it was enough for Emilia to shut up.

*

“I’m home,” Y/N said happily as she entered the house and closed the door behind her.

It was almost 9 pm when she returned. Both her uncle and aunt were cuddled up on the couch, binge watching some tv shows. Ice Cream was peacefully snoozing on the floor- however she woke up just the second she heard Y/N’s voice.

Y/N’s college had ended a long time ago but she decided to go to a coffee shop to finish an assignment that she had. Or maybe she just didn’t want to see Harry’s face or be in his presence at all -everything about him annoyed her, even thinking about him for a split second made her scrunch her nose in annoyance. Y/N knew she shouldn’t be this judgmental as she met him just the night before and for couple of minutes only. But she couldn’t help herself, something about him just made her not like him.

As Y/N expected she hadn’t ran into Harry in the coffee shop, nonetheless she had ran into Tom.

Y/N was typing away furiously on her laptop when he had approached her. Y/N had her eyebrows knitted together; her notebook was carelessly lying near her with all the bullet points about the assignment.

“May I sit here,” Tom had said, but Y/N was too busy to recognize his voice. She was about shoo away whoever it was, but that was until she realized who it was.

Y/N had looked at his face for a while. A bit shocked - not expecting to see him there and then contemplating whether to say yes or not.

“Uh yeah,” she had stuttered out after a while gesturing to the sit across her. Tom had happily sat down and started a conversation about college and what she was doing. At first it was just about college but then they started talking about personal stuffs -what they liked, what they didn’t, their families.

By 8, they had another mug of hot chocolate and Tom ended up sitting next to her in excuse of seeing what she was doing.

Y/N had finished half of the assignment after sitting there for five hours. Y/N knew she would’ve finished the whole thing, if Tom hadn’t interrupted but she wasn’t complaining - she had a little crush on him after all.

“Welcome home, Y/N,” Clare said from the couch.

“Someone’s glowing, what happened?” Jake asked seeing the bright smile on her face.

“Nothing,” she shook her head, but she couldn’t shake of the huge smile.

“C'mere, Iccy!” Y/N gestured Ice Cream to follow her upstairs, who was on her feet almost instantly, moving her tail happily.

Y/N slowly made her way up the stairs, Ice Cream hot on her trail.

“You missed me, buddy?” Y/N said looking down at the 3 years old Samoyed as she earned a loud bark from her.

Y/N laughed. She knew how clingy she was and she knew the only thing Ice Cream wanted to do then was cuddle her. And she didn’t mind that. Y/N was about to take the turn towards her room but that is when she smashed into something hard making her stumble a little backward; the back of her leg coming in contact with Ice Creams body made her lose control. She was about fall on her butt and probably over Ice Cream but Y/N quickly grabbed the stairs railing as Ice Cream moved away from her spot.

“I’m so sorry! Are you okay?” Harry asked. He had both of his hands extended towards her - probably to grab her incase she hadn’t gotten hold of the railings. He wore a horrified look on his face.

“Was okay,” Y/N mumbled walking past Harry and into her room.

“Hey, I’m really sorry about that wasn’t looking where I was going,” Harry said. But the moment Ice Cream had entered her room, she quickly shut the door without looking up at him.

And there, she shut the door on his face for the second time, leaving him clueless in the hallway.

She really didn’t like him.

“I don’t think I have to tell you this, but -”

Y/N was trying to stuff few of her books in her bag when Jake spoke.

“Hm?” Y/N didn’t look up at him, she was too busy with her books and her bag.

“Stay away from Harry.”

Y/N came to an halt hearing that.

“Huh?” she was confused really, why was her uncle saying that, all of a sudden. She clearly remembered the ‘she’s off limit’ thing he said to Harry, but Jake also knew she didn’t really like him

“What are you talking about,” she returned to zip her bag full of books. She was pretty sure her shoulder would be sore for carrying it but she had to return those books to the college library by that day.

“Harry, he- just stay away from him,” Jake said again.

“Why? I mean isn’t he ‘such a nice guy’,” Y/N said nonchalantly, not bothering to look up at him.

“He is but, you know - there’s media involved, and his fans can be pretty aggressive and I don’t think it’ll work out. I mean he’s good guy but I don’t want you to get hurt ag-” Jake rambled on but Y/N quickly cut him off.

“Okay, calm down,” she hung the bag on her back and let out a groan. It was heavier than she thought it’d be.“I’m really not interested.”

“Where is the ‘nice guy’, anyway?” She made her way towards the door

“He had work in his studio.”

Y/N nodded, but she truly didn’t care.

“See you later,” she called.

She heard Jake and Clare both call back from inside the house before she shut the door.

“What?” Y/N asked clearly clueless as she flipped few pages of the new book she just took from the library shelf.

“It’s fun,” she replied.

body:
Yesterday a very good friend of mine (who only listens to rock and indie rock and has absolutely no idea about one direction) started humming Kiwi when she saw it in my recently played list.

She had no idea who Harry Styles was prior to his solo career and just said she heard the song and loved it instantly, and she proceeded to say he is veeeery good looking. and when I said how he would be the perfect boyfried material, guess what her first assumption was? “Too bad he’s gay”.

In other news our boy is a rockstar and everyone but his own fans knows he’s not exactly what you call straight.
